track_notes: This is such an easy route to MI-001 from the large car park where there is a restaurant. You can also obtain refreshments and snacks from a mountain house just below the summit (5 mins from summit to house). We took 53 minutes to reach the top. There are two viewing positions with a fence around each. Summit is visited by many tourists on holiday. 301m ascent with 2.7 Km to walk one way.
track_title: Cobbled track from car park at Achada Do Teixeira

track_notes:
Pico Ruivo is reached most easily from Achada do Teixeira on a paved walkway. This here is a more scening route through the Madeira heartland.

Park at Pico do Arieiro (Big parking lot for tourists, souvenir stands, food & beverages) and
follow the marked trail. It leads downhill initially. Take an electric  flashlight with you! The trail uses several sections of underground passages! Carry enough water and clothing to protect from wind! Spectacular scenery all along the way. This tour ist described in all printed hiking guides of Madeira and it sure is the highlight of hiking Madeira!
 
At the summit I tied my mast to one of the handrails at the southern view-point. Very, very crowded summit, but most of the visitors ascend via the shorter route from Achada do Teixeira!

I activated Pico di Arieiro in the afternoon when we came back to the parking lot.
track_title: Pico Ruivo from Pico do Arieio

track_notes:
Sem duvida o trilho mais bonito que fiz at hoje!!!
Deve estar preparado fisicamente, levar lanterna (tuneis), roupa adequada porque na Ilha da Madeira um dia pode ter as 4 estaes, bastante gua.
Para meu desagrado nunca estive sozinho no trilho, havia imensas pessoas... Talvez no Inverno seja melhor:). Para no voltar para trs (XYL :)) usei os servios de uma empresa de transferes das muitas que existem na Madeira.
Podia ir ao Pico Ruivo a partir da Teixeira? Podia, mas no era a mesma coisa! :)
